# Cursor Rules

## Project Structure
- `src/` folder is where all code should be written
- Keep README.md updated with project progress and changes

## File Management
- Do not create or delete files without asking the user first
- Always confirm before making structural changes to the project

## Code Quality
- Follow clean code principles
- Do not write comments in code
- Code should be simple, clean, and self-explanatory
- Variable names and function names should be descriptive and self-explanatory
- Prefer clarity over brevity in naming

